				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2913401/scp-3071#post-3973537</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 17 Sep 2018 12:19:53 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Agent Arrack</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1773725</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>As others have stated, this is clean and nice but lacks narrative and actual &quot;scariness&quot;.</p> <p>A suggestion would be to hint more at the backstory, as I guess there's some obscure theme here?</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2913401#post-3947358</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2913401/scp-3071#post-3947358</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 31 Aug 2018 22:24:25 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>DoctorNovakaine</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3003380</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I have to downvote. It's&#8230;a collection of random unexplained events that doesn't tie together in any way. There's no narrative here, when there was clearly intended to be a narrative. Dude disappeared. Cabin gives people a worse version of Locked-in Syndrome. It inexplicably expands, because we need to meet our quota of Foundation slaughter. There's a letter that has no explanation or relevance to the rest of the story. And then suddenly it's over because Anomalous Jack randomly attacks a researcher for no clear reason.</p> <p>These are all checkpoints in an outline. But that's all that's there. Nothing fills it in. We don't even know why Anomalous Jack calls it &quot;The Orphanage.&quot; It feels like this could go somewhere interesting, but as it currently stands, it's not.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2913401#post-3825757</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2913401/scp-3071#post-3825757</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 05 Jun 2018 19:10:34 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>DrFred</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1377450</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>No Vote for me.</p> <p>It leaves me curious to know more&#8230;.the letter is the best part, but there isn't any meat on that hook. Without more on the Orphanage, or why they are becoming trapped in their own minds, or who the first person is, or who the second person is&#8230;.there just isn't anything presented there and the hints don't give enough info.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2913401#post-3589061</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2913401/scp-3071#post-3589061</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 10 Sep 2017 19:45:02 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Volttekka</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2845469</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This SCP denies me the ability to make sense of it. It basically is &quot;creepy cabin in the forest what locks you out of your body&quot; with nothing to really hint at <em>why</em> it happens.<br /> The stuff with the mysterious figure and the note were a nice move in the right direction, but a confrontation happens without any real payoff, and the story fully ends there.<br /> It's like a jigsaw puzzle with only the border pieces, you get a feel for the general shape of the whole, but the meat of it is missing.</p> <p>Just my opinion, though.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
